column4: I tried to upgrade to the stable release and had a crash and now when im trying to upgrade i get this error:
An upgrade from 'precise' to 'oneiric' is not supported with this tool
Why didn't you upgrade to 12.04
It crased during upgrade from ________ to _________ ?
What did you have installed when you started?  What do you have now?  lsb_release -r
now i have 11.10
what does   lsb_release -r   return?
Ok, first do this: sudo apt-get update ; sudo apt-get -f install
i get this error when I try the first one: E: Could not get lock /var/lib/dpkg/lock - open (11: Resource temporarily unavailable)
Sounds like you have another application running that uses apt.  Look and see.
how
Do you have the Update Manager open?
how do i kill it?
If it is update-manager, you could try: sudo pkill update-manager
But it may leave the lock file if you do.
what do i do then?
ps aux |grep update
